{
  "commit_id": 2,
  "subject": "[common] Get null count from Arrow metadata instead of statistics",
  "message": "[common] Get null count from Arrow metadata instead of statistics\n\nIntroduce V2 statistics format that omits null counts from the binary\nstatistics layout. Instead, null counts are extracted on-demand from\nArrow RecordBatch FlatBuffer metadata via the new ArrowNullCountReader.\n\nThis reduces the serialized statistics size and avoids redundant null\ncount tracking during record writing, since Arrow already maintains\naccurate null counts in its field node metadata.\n\nKey changes:\n- Add ArrowNullCountReader to extract null counts from Arrow FlatBuffer\n- Introduce STATISTICS_VERSION_V2 that excludes null counts from layout\n- Update writer/parser/collector to handle V2 format\n- Make DefaultLogRecordBatchStatistics support lazy null count injection\n- Maintain backward compatibility: V1 statistics are still parsed correctly\n- Add comprehensive tests including V1 backward compatibility verification",
  "type": "extractive",
  "skip_gan": false,
